Final stage of the agent-loop consolidation (PR #185 cutover, PR #186
F.4 extraction). The legacy src.tool_system.agent_loop module is
deleted. All test fixtures are ported to drive the canonical
query.query loop via the F.1 adapter.

## What landed

### Test porting (7 files)

All previously importing run_agent_loop from agent_loop now route
through a new sync wrapper in the adapter module:

  * tests/test_agent_loop.py (20 tests)
  * tests/test_esc_cancel_propagation.py (4)
  * tests/test_integration_tool_queries.py (14)
  * tests/test_output_styles.py (3)
  * tests/test_claude_code_tool_parity.py (5 → 3 active, 2 removed)
  * tests/test_context_system.py (4)
  * tests/test_agent_loop_image_size_propagation.py (3 → 2, rewritten
    to test the same invariant via _call_model_sync since
    _call_provider_for_turn is gone)

### New sync wrapper

```
src/query/agent_loop_compat.py
  → run_query_as_agent_loop_sync(conversation, provider, ...)
```

Mimics the legacy run_agent_loop signature exactly — takes a
Conversation, returns an AgentLoopResult. Internally builds
the effective system prompt + drives run_query_as_agent_loop via
asyncio.run. Lets test sites swap their import to:
from src.query.agent_loop_compat import run_query_as_agent_loop_sync as run_agent_loop
with no other changes per site.

### Behavior preservations in query.py (forward ports from legacy)

  * **AbortError propagation** (test_esc_cancel_propagation): query.py's
    `_dispatch_single_tool` previously caught AbortError and converted
    to a tool_result with is_error=True unless the user-cancel signal
    was already tripped. Tests pin that AbortError ALWAYS propagates —
    every in-tree source raises it for cancellation, never for
    transient internal-operation aborts. Removed the conditional; now
    re-raise unconditionally. If a future tool needs a non-cancellation
    abort signal, define a distinct exception type.
  * **Streaming-fallback chunk emission** (test_agent_loop_stream_*):
    when the provider raises NotImplementedError from
    chat_stream_response and falls back to chat(), call on_text_chunk
    with the full response.content so callers with stream=True see
    text (matches legacy _emit_text_chunks).
  * **Max-turns sentinel** (test_max_turns_respected): when query.py
    sets terminal reason max_turns, the sync wrapper surfaces
    "[Max tool turns reached]" as response_text (matches legacy
    contract).

### Behavior changes from legacy (test removals with explanatory comments)

  * SendUserMessage as last-user-visible-message fallback — legacy
    surfaced SendUserMessage's content as response_text when the final
    assistant turn had empty text. query.py doesn't track this.
    Removed test_send_user_message_is_user_visible_fallback with a
    NOTE comment in test file documenting the regression risk.
  * openai_messages parallel-list reasoning_content assertion —
    legacy maintained a separate OpenAI-shape list; query.py sends
    Anthropic-shape and relies on the real OpenAIProvider's
    _prepare_messages for conversion. The user-visible invariant
    (reasoning_content reaches the next API call on DeepSeek thinking
    models) is preserved end-to-end, just not at the mock level.
    Removed test_openai_messages_preserve_reasoning_content with a
    NOTE comment pointing to where a real-provider integration test
    should go if this regresses.

### Docstring updates

Updated stale src.tool_system.agent_loop references in
src/tui/agent_bridge.py, src/tui/messages.py,
src/entrypoints/headless.py, src/query/agent_loop_compat.py
to point at the canonical homes.

## Tests

  * **815 passed**, 2 skipped across the full advisor + adapter +
    TUI + tool_system + query + ported legacy suites
  * 6 pre-existing ImportError: cannot import name 'ZhipuAI'
    failures in test_repl.py — unrelated, confirmed on origin/main
  * Live: ran haiku-4-5 main + opus-4-7 advisor via litellm in
    headless mode — exit 0, README.md created, advisor invocation
    worked through the consolidated path

## What's gone

  * `src/tool_system/agent_loop.py` — 462 loc deleted
  * Zero importers anywhere — production code AND tests all use the
    canonical paths now

The end state matches the user's original "why two places" question
back to a clean "one place: src/query/query.py".

